# data_carpentry_notes
Notes made available for data carpentry sessions run at ESR during June 2019.

Here is the link to the main workshop page: https://esr-nz.github.io/2019-06-25-DC-ESR-KSC/

This is the link to the etherpad: https://pad.carpentries.org/2019-06-25-DC-ESR-KSC

## data

If you want to download the cleaned, complete survey data use:

```R
download.file(url = "https://github.com/sirselim/data_carpentry_notes/blob/master/data_output/surveys_complete.csv", 
              destfile = "data/surveys_complete.csv", mode = "wb")
```

## useful links

  - The R Graph Gallery: https://www.r-graph-gallery.com/
    - get inspired by some really awesome plots!
  - Graph Cookbook: http://www.cookbook-r.com/Graphs/index.html
  - Data to Viz : https://www.data-to-viz.com/caveats.html
    - this site helps you select the 'right' plot for you data
  - cowplot: https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/cowplot/vignettes/introduction.html
  - viridis: https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/viridis/vignettes/intro-to-viridis.html
  - Esquisse (R package): https://github.com/dreamRs/esquisse
    - a plugin for RStudio that allows you create ggplot2 plots interactively.
  - R for Data Science [book]: https://r4ds.had.co.nz/
  - datapasta: https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/datapasta/vignettes/how-to-datapasta.html
    - pasting your tables into various R formats

-----

Please feel free to download and modify as you wish.

Full credit to Data Carpentry: https://datacarpentry.org/

